node.text:
You have to pick one of these leaps of faith… which do you choose? 😳
1. The Pendulum Jump, Avencal 🇧🇷
2. Cachoeira da Fumaça 🇧🇷

Brazil is know for many things but did you know they had adrenaline pumping attractions like this!?

The first, is a 2.5-second free fall which takes place over the Avencal Waterfall, a beautiful sight that’s 100 meters high and located 10 km away from the city center of Urubici, in the mountain range of Santa Catarina.

The second clip shows one of the most impressive waterfalls in Brazil know as the Cachoeira da Fumaça.
This waterfall has a height of about 45 meters and is one of the most sought-after attractions in the municipality of Nova Ponte. Once you get to the top, you'll be greeted by an incredible vantage point that offers lush views of the surrounding forest. 🇧🇷

🎥 @fragatafpv
Vid 2 @escolhas_de_simone

node.text:
Who else wants to try this in Japan?welcome to Hirobun, a laid-back riverside restaurant in Kyoto’s Kurama and Kibune district. If you're up for a gastronomic Japan trip, bookmark this! 😋🍜

"What you see here is Nagashi Somen, which is a special way of serving thin white noodles. The noodles travel down a sliced bamboo pipe with flowing cold water. You then have to catch the noodles with chopsticks before they pass by you or are snatched up by someone else. There is also a cold dipping sauce that you dunk them in before eating (as seen performed immaculately by Kate). Lastly, when the red noodles come out it means your time is over."

If you’re worrying about hygiene, don’t fret: the bamboo is changed every batch, the leftover noodles will not be recycled, and the staff assigns one flume per group—which means you will only be sharing your flume among your company.🎋❤️

Who else wants to try this in Japan? 🇯🇵

🎥 @kotravellers 
📍 Kyoto, Japan
🎶 Yoshida Brothers - Fukaki Umi No Kanata

node.text:
Dip anyone? 💦 If you're looking for the finest rooftop spaces in London, soak up this world-famous Sky Pool that seems to float in the air. 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿

Located in the Nine Elms district, this exclusive 25-meter-long pool connects two blocks of apartments. Built by structural engineers Eckersley O'Callaghan and designed by HAL Architects, it's known as the world's first floating transparent 'sky pool'. 💦

Did you know this pool existed in London and would you take a dip in it? 😄

🎥 @hobopeeba
📍 London, England

node.text:
Pet dog, pat cat or pet giraffes? 🦒Hanging out with friendly giants in Nairobi, a destination known for its beautiful national parks and diverse wildlife. 😍

Set in the Langata suburb of Nairobi and shot in Giraffe Manor, this incredible footage shows the inquisitive nature of these beautiful and gentle giants. Giraffes live primarily in savanna areas in the sub-Saharan region of Africa and are known to be friendly and social animals by nature.🦒

What’s your favourite safari animal?

🎥 @_khloe.g 
Vid 2 @venelin_k & @inagallardo_adamand

node.text:
Who says mermaids don’t exist!? 🥰 I bet the manatee was just as surprised as @shellseaflmermaid 🧜‍♀️ 

Besides the pristine water and swarm of fish in this natural Florida spring, the manatee's surprise appearance makes this footage even more incredible. 🇺🇸 Great shot @themikerioux 🙌

Manatees are curious by nature and often initiate interaction with humans; so if you happen to see manatees while swimming, snorkeling, diving, or boating, it's important to avoid doing anything disruptive. You can "look but don't touch" while practicing passive observation from a distance, avoid excessive noise and splashing, and resist the urge to feed them. (source: savethemanatee.org) ✔️

Have you ever seen a manatee before? 😍

🎥 @themikerioux
🧜‍♀️ @shellseaflmermaid
📍 Florida, US
🎶 Kathleen - Pure Imagination
